The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, August 30, 2005 

 New secretary to CM

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, Aug. 29: The government today effected a shuffle in the ranks of its IAS officers.

 As part of the move, municipal and hill affairs secretary Dipankar Mukherjee was appointed principal secretary to the chief minister. Arun Bhattacharya, the incumbent, will retire on August 31. 

 Calcutta Municipal Corporation commissioner Debashish Som will succeed Mukherjee. After Soms exit, Alapan Bandopadhyay, now director, industries, will take over as the new commissioner.

 Dilip Chakraborty, who is now principal secretary in the cooperation department, will hold additional charge of principal secretary in the information and cultural affairs department. 

 Sports and youth services secretary Ashok Patnaik has been transferred to the forest department. R.K. Tripathy, who now holds additional charge as forest secretary, will officiate only as managing director, Housing Infrastructure Development Corporation (Hidco).

 Special secretary, transport, K.N. Behera has been posted as principal secretary, sports and youth affairs department. 

 Ravi Kant, now special secretary in information technology department, has been posted as labour commissioner. Satish Chandra Tiwary, the labour commissioner, will be the new principal secretary in the technical education department. J. Sundara Sekhar, who now holds charge of principal secretary of the technical education department, has been shifted to the mass education department. 

 K. John Koshy, the principal secretary of mass education, has been transferred to water resources. R. Bandopadhyay, who held the charge earlier, is now in Delhi as additional secretary to the Union ministry of transport.




